## Atlantis — Detailed Setup

### PR Conventions

- **1 PR = 1 layer** — keep changes scoped to a single layer per PR
- PR title format: `<layer>: <description>` (e.g., `connectivity: add bastion host`)

### Atlantis Commands (comment on PR)

| Command | Effect |
|---|---|
| `atlantis plan` | Re-run plan for this PR |
| `atlantis apply` | Apply after required approvals |
| `atlantis unlock` | Release plan lock |

### Approval Flow

1. Open PR → Atlantis auto-plans (configured in `atlantis.yaml`)
2. Review plan output in PR comment
3. Get required approvals (`apply_requirements: [approved, mergeable]`)
4. Comment `atlantis apply` → Atlantis applies in CAF layer order

### Server Setup

Configure your Atlantis server with:
- Webhook secret → GitHub/ADO repo settings
- Azure credentials → env vars (`ARM_CLIENT_ID`, `ARM_TENANT_ID`, `ARM_SUBSCRIPTION_ID`)
- WIF (recommended): `ARM_USE_OIDC=true` with federated credential

See [Atlantis docs](https://www.runatlantis.io/docs/) for server installation.
